A yearly subscription is refundable within 14 days of purchase and includes a 365-day membership. Elsewhere, fuels and chemicals producer Sasol sank for a second day, dropping as much as 4.1%, as crude oil prices weakened. South Africa’s government will curb alcohol sales and close some of the nation’s beaches at the height of the summer-holiday season, among a series of new restrictions to rein in surging coronavirus infections. The country is fast-approaching 1 million infections, with 866,127 people having contracted the disease so far, President Cyril Ramaphosa said on Monday. South African markets will be shut on Wednesday for the Day of Reconciliation public holiday. Foreigners were net buyers of South African stocks for a seventh day on Monday, purchasing R680 million ($45 million) of local equities, according to exchange operator JSE Ltd. © 2020 Bloomberg